Prenatal diagnosis of a tetraploid fetus. A tetraploid fetus with an unusual facial appearance and multiple congenital anomalies (large cerebral lateral ventricles lung, cardiac, and genital abnormalities) is reported. Chromosome analysis was performed on amniocytes and fetal blood lymphocytes. A comparison is made with other reported cases (nine liveborn infants and one 17.2-week-old fetus).